definition.value: Any collection of muscles that is part of a pectoral complex. The pectoral complex comprises the pectoral girdle and the associated limb or fin.
Any muscle organ that is part of a pectoral appendage (forelimb or pectoral fin).
Any muscle organ that is part of a pelvic appendage (hindlimb or pelvic fin).
A ring of fibrous tissue surrounding the optic nerve at its entrance at the apex of the orbit.
Chorda tendinea which is attached to the leaflet of mitral valve and is continuous with the endocardium of papillary muscle of left ventricle.
Chorda tendinea which is attached to the leaflet of tricuspid valve and is continuous with the endocardium of papillary muscle of right ventricle.
White matter that is part of a brainstem [Automatically generated definition].

A muscle organ that consists of skeletal muscle tissue ensheathed in epimysium, that develops from myotome and that is innervated by some somatic motor neuron. Skeletal muscles are typically attached (via a tendon) to a bone but there are exceptions (e.g. intrinsic tongue muscles).

A muscle structure of invertebrates whose origin and insertion sites are in basal side of the epidermis or structures derived from it. The simplest somatic muscles consist of a single cell and associated extracellular structures.
A somatic muscle that consists of one or more somatic muscle myotubes and any associated extracellular structures.
A portion of tissue that will develop into vasculature.
One of the primary blood vessel sprouts that originate from the dorsal aorta and posterior cardinal vein and align dorsoventrally at the myotomal boundaries between somites.
The space between a blood vessel and the pia mater.
The major preaxial endochondral element in the posterior zeugopod[Phenoscape].
A vertebral endochondral element in the cervical region of the vertebral column.
A vertebral endochondral element in the thoracic region of the vertebral column.
The major postaxial endochondral element in the posterior zeugopod[Phenoscape].
